cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.SE 

The paper focuses on the application of Recurrent Neural Network models for detecting anomalous behavior of the CERN superconducting magnets. This falls under the category of machine learning and neural networks, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the development of a custom detector and the selection of detector parameters, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence, covered by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with the detection of anomalous behavior in a complex system, which falls under the category of systems and control, covered by cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves the design and implementation of the adaptive signal quantization algorithm, which falls under the category of software engineering, covered by cs.SE (Software Engineering).
